      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2020-06-18</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2021-05-14T18:07:19Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Count the Crimes to Cut Act of 2020</b></p> <p>This bill requires certain reports on federal criminal statutory and regulatory offenses.</p> <p>Specifically, the Department of Justice (DOJ) must report to Congress a list of all criminal statutory offenses and the potential criminal penalty, the number of prosecutions brought by DOJ each year for the previous 15 years, and the <i>mens rea </i>(i.e., guilty mind) requirement for each offense. Further, the bill requires each specified federal agency to provide Congress with a similar list of all criminal regulatory offenses that are enforced by the agency.</p> <p> Finally, the bill requires DOJ and each specified federal agency to establish a publicly accessible index of the crimes that are reported to Congress.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
